Mexican Stocks: Cemex, Homex, Televisa Gain; Penoles Retreats

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-04-01T21:05:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-01/mexican-stocks-cemex-homex-televisa-gain-penoles-retreats.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m.  New York  time.  The IPC index rose 0.9 percent to 37,775.07.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO MM), the largest cement maker in the
Americas, rose 2 percent to 10.84 pesos as payrolls climbed in
the company’s second-biggest market. U.S. payrolls increased by
216,000 workers last month after a revised 194,000 gain the
prior month, the Labor Department said today in  Washington .  Genomma Lab Internacional SAB (LABB MM), the Mexican
producer of over-the-counter drugs, advanced 3.6 percent to
27.89 pesos. The company said it got a  bank loan  for as much as
2 billion pesos, according to a filing today to the Mexican
stock exchange.  Grupo Televisa SA (TLEVICPO)  , the world’s largest
Spanish-language broadcaster, advanced 1.7 percent to 59.41
pesos. Televisa agreed to acquire full ownership of its Cablemas
SA unit in a deal valued at 4.7 billion pesos ($397 million),
getting the 42 percent portion of the company it didn’t already
own, according to a filing today with Mexico’s stock exchange.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, dropped 1.5 percent to 431.49 pesos. Silver for
May delivery in New York retreated 0.3 percent to $37.760 an
ounce.  Homebuilders advanced after Credit Suisse Group AG
suggested moving exposure away from Mexico’s cyclical stocks
such as mining companies into sectors such as homebuilding that
will benefit from the domestic economic recovery.  Desarrolladora Homex SAB (HOMEX* MM), Mexico’s largest
homebuilder, climbed 5.4 percent to 57.01 pesos.  Corp. GEO SAB (GEOB MM), Mexico’s second-largest
homebuilder, rose 3.8 percent to 34.59 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
